<DOC><DOCNO> AP890503-0174 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-03-89 1749EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-Pepper     05-03 0145</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Pepper,140</SECOND><HEAD>Pepper Changes Hospitals for Care</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Rep. Claude Pepper, the eldest member ofCongress, has entered Johns Hopkins Hospital in Baltimore where hecan be under the care of a prominent specialist in gastrointestinalproblems, his office said Wednesday.   The 88-year-old Pepper, D-Fla., had been under treatment for a``digestive disturbance'' at Walter Reed Medical Center since April6 before checking into Johns Hopkins on Tuesday, his office said.   The announcement said Pepper consulted Dr. John H. Hendrix onApril 25 at the physician's office at Johns Hopkins andsubsequently decided to place himself under Hendrix' care.   President Bush visited with Pepper for about 20 minutes lastSunday.   The announcement from Pepper's office said, ``While Pepperappreciates the many inquiries and good wishes he has received, hehas decided to release no further information about his health atthis time.''</TEXT></DOC>